commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0 of the iP + Added greeting and exit messages as a skeletal programme
Level 1 of the iP + Added a messageHandler method that merely echoes the user's input messages.

Level 2 of the iP + Edited the messageHandler method to store all tasks inputted by the user accordingly. + Added a new DukeList class that stores and manages all messages given by the user. + The DukeList class contains the store and display methods which stores tasks inputted by the user and displays them in a list accordingly.

Level 3 of the iP + Edited the messageHandler method in the Duke class to support marking and unmarking tasks. + Added a new Task class that stores a single task inputted by the user. + The DukeList class contains the mark and unmark methods which respectively marks and unmarks the current tasks  stored in the DukeList class.

+ Level - 4 Added Todo, Deadline and Event subclasses which inherit from Task.
commitResults.messageBody:
+ Updated the messageHandler method in Duke to parse the commands given by the user to store specific tasks and their deadlines, if any.

+ Updated DukeList to overload its store methods, to accomodate to the different subclasses of Task.

Add a new DataSaver class
commitResults.messageBody:
The DataSaver class handles all saving and loading of tasks
in a test.s file.

The test.s file has the relative path of /data/data.s. This
makes it user-friendly across multiple platforms.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add a new Parser and DateAndTime classes
commitResults.messageBody:
The new Parser class helps to parse commands given into the Duke class and also
helps to format date and times given to the Duke class.

This is done for OOP purposes, to help encapsulate tasks in managing messages received
by the Duke class.
